Merge pull request #14 from edunham/certs

Switch from Moz IT certs to ACM-issued certs

Switch from Moz IT certs to ACM-issued certs

https://www.terraform.io/docs/providers/aws/d/acm_certificate.html leads me to
believe that this is the correct syntax for switching from the "imported"
certs to the "amazon issued" certs.

It is important to switch to the amazon issued certs because renewal goes:

* Request new cert
* Have someone subscribed to hostmaster@mozilla.com click the link to approve
* Use new cert (though I do not yet know how to tell Terraform to take the
  newer of multiple amazon issued certs; we can sort that out next year)

As opposed to the old way where moz IT generated the cert and gpg'd it up and
emailed it to me, with me as a SPOF.
